New `starknet-hardhat-plugin` version (v0.4.2) has been released:
https://github.com/Shard-Labs/starknet-hardhat-plugin/releases/tag/v0.4.2
- Introduce utility functions for handling L1-L2 communication (postman message exchange with Devnet): @maciejka 
  - `starknet.devnet.loadL1MessagingContract` - for loading an L1 contract that exchanges messages between L1 and L2
  - `starknet.devnet.flush` - for propagating messages to the other layer
  - Basic example: https://github.com/Shard-Labs/starknet-hardhat-plugin#test---l1-l2-communication-message-exchange-with-devnet
  - Complex example: https://github.com/Shard-Labs/starknet-hardhat-example/blob/master/test/postman.test.ts#L91

- Introduce an `Account` class for invoking/calling contract functions through a Starknet account. Create `Account` using utility functions:
  - `starknet.deployAccountFromABI` - for new Account deployment
  - `starknet.getAccountFromAddress` - for loading a predeployed Account
  - Basic example: https://github.com/Shard-Labs/starknet-hardhat-plugin#test---accounts
  - Complex example: https://github.com/Shard-Labs/starknet-hardhat-example/blob/master/test/account-test.ts

